OIL WELL SUPPLY COMPANY et al. v. WASHOMA PETROLEUM COMPANY. No. 1076. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. July 20, 1934. J. II. Foster, of Dallas, Tex., and Ayres, Cowan, MeCorkle & Fair, of Wichita, Kan., for appellants. Vermilion, Evans, Carey & Lilleston, of Wichita, Kan., and Albert L. MeRill, of Oklahoma City, Okl., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on stipulation.
